SIMPLE: salicylal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salicylal
<hw>Sal"i*cyl`al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Salicyl</ets>ic + <ets>al</ets>dehide.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A thin, fragrant, colorless oil,
<chform>HO.C6H4.CHO</chform>, found in the flowers of meadow sweet
(<gen>Spiraea</gen>), and also obtained by oxidation of salicin,
saligenin, etc. It reddens on exposure. Called also
<altname>salicylol</altname>, <altname>salicylic aldehyde</altname>, and
formerly <altname>salicylous acid</altname> <it>or</it>
<altname>spiroylous acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salicylate</ent>⟦br⟧
